           <div class="taxonomy-term-description">News and announcements<br />
</div><div id="node-3788" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-sticky node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/3788" title="This week in Spring  - 22 January, 2013 ">This week in Spring  - 22 January, 2013 </a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Josh Long on Mon, 2013-01-21 18:01        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_14 first last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/14" rel="tag" title="">This Week in Spring</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p> Welcome to another installment of <EM>This Week in Spring</EM>!  
	As usual, we've got a lot to cover, so let's get to it! 
	</P>
	<ol>
		
			  <LI> The future is now and it has a name and version - <EM>Spring 4.0</EM>. <a href="http://blog.springsource.org/2013/01/16/next-stop-spring-framework-4-0/">Juergen Hoeller outlined the proposed next iteration of Spring, Spring Framework 4.0</a>!  </LI>	
			
        <li>If you missed the live webinar of the Spring Framework 3.2 GA release, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fb5YG2W1srA">check out the replay</a>, which also has a brief discussion Spring Framework 4.0.</li>
        <li> Costin Leau has announced that <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3787">Spring for Apache Hadoop 1.0 RC2 is now available</a>! The new release includes  dedicated namespace support for Cascading, enhanced compatibility with Cloudera CDH3 and 4,  
        enhanced integration with Spring Batch and Hadoop, safer job cancellation and improved documentation. </li>
        <li>Andrew Clement announced that <a href= "http://blog.springsource.org/2013/01/08/scripted-editor-0-3-release-available/">the 0.3 release of the Scripted editor is now available</a>.  There are many new features, including easier installation (now available through Node Package Manager - <code>npm</code>). </li>
              <li> Roy Clarkson has announced that <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3784"> Spring Mobile 1.1.0.M2 has been released</a> with many new features including a   Spring MVC <code>ViewResolver</code> that resolves the view based on <code>Device</code> and <code>SitePreference</code>, and then forwards to the correct, delegate <code>ViewResolver</code>. </li>
        <li>Join Scott Andrews as he discusses the role of Javascript in an exciting webinar on  January 24, 2013: <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3767" title="Webinar: Architecture of a Modern Web App"> Architecture of a Modern Web App</a>. </li>
        <li>Join Brian Cavalier and John Hann as they discuss Inversion of Control (IoC) and Javascript in a Webinar on January 31, 2013: <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3768">IOC + Javascript</a>.</li>
        <li> Martin Lippert, Andy Clement, and Andrew Eisenberg's presentation from 
        SpringOne2GX 2012, <a href= "http://www.infoq.com/presentations/Tools-JavaScript-Orion-Scripted">
        <EM>Tooling for the JavaScript era</EM></a>, is now available online from InfoQ.     </li>
        <li> The SpringOne 2GX 2012    replay of <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3783"> <em>Automated Provisioning of Spring Applications to EC2 and VMware Cloud</em></a> is now available. </li>
        <li> Nicolas Frankel has a nice post on how <a href="http://blog.frankel.ch/dry-your-spring-beans-configuration-file">to inherit configuration from parent bean definitions  to reduce redundant configuration</a>. Nice!  </li>
        <li> Arnaud Cogoluègnes has a nice post on <A href="http://blog.zenika.com/index.php?post/2013/01/15/spring-mvc-test-framework">how to use the Spring MVC test framework</a> </li>
        <li> Taking the example further, Arnaud also shows how to <a href="http://blog.zenika.com/index.php?post/2013/01/15/REST-Web-Services-testing-with-Spring-MVC">test Spring MVC REST controllers using the Spring MVC test framework</a>.   </li>
        <li> Tomasz Nurkiewicz has put together <a href= "http://nurkiewicz.blogspot.de/2013/01/spring-data-jdbc-generic-dao.html">
        a Spring Data Repository implementation for JDBC</a>. That's really cool! I can't wait to give this a try!        </li>
        <li>  Tobias Fiohre has a nice 
        introduction to the ideas  enabled by <A href="http://blog.codecentric.de/en/2013/01/a-real-roca-using-bootstrap-jquery-thymeleaf-spring-hateoas-and-spring-mvc/">Spring HATEOAS (<EM>ROCA</EM>, or resource-oriented client architectures)
          complete with a sample application and code</a>! Nicely done, Tobias!</li>
</ol> 
  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
<div id="node-3787" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-sticky node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/3787" title="Spring for Apache Hadoop 1.0 RC2 Released">Spring for Apache Hadoop 1.0 RC2 Released</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Costin Leau on Mon, 2013-01-21 12:17        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_4 first last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/4" rel="tag" title="News and announcements
">News and Announcements</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>Dear Spring Community,<br />
I am pleased to announce the second, and last planned, release candidate, 1.0 RC2 for Spring for Apache Hadoop:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.springsource.com/download/community?project=Spring%20Data%20Hadoop&amp;version=1.0.0.RC2">Downloads</a> | <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-data/hadoop/docs/1.0.0.RC2/api/">JavaDocs</a> | <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-data/hadoop/docs/1.0.0.RC2/reference/html/">Reference Documentation</a> | <a href="http://static.springframework.org/spring-data/hadoop/docs/1.0.0.RC2/changelog.txt">Changelog</a></p>
<p>RC2 provides bug fixes and improvements and enhances the overall usability:</p>
  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first"></li>
<li class="node_read_more last"><a href="/node/3787" title="Read the rest of Spring for Apache Hadoop 1.0 RC2 Released.">Read more</a></li>
</ul>
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
<div id="node-3785" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-sticky node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/spring-mobile/news/1.1.0.m2-released" title="Spring Mobile 1.1.0.M2 Released">Spring Mobile 1.1.0.M2 Released</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Roy Clarkson on Thu, 2013-01-17 12:16        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_4 first last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/4" rel="tag" title="News and announcements
">News and Announcements</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>Dear Spring Community,</p>

<p>We are happy to announce the release of <a href="http://www.springsource.org/spring-mobile">Spring Mobile</a> 1.1.0.M2!</p>

<p>Spring Mobile provides extensions to Spring MVC that aid in the development of cross-platform mobile web applications.</p>

<p>This release adds LiteDeviceDelegatingViewResolver, a ViewResolver implementation that adjusts the view name based on Device and SitePreference. It then delegates to another ViewResolver to complete the process of resolving the view. This release is built and tested against Spring Framework 3.2. See the <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-mobile/docs/1.1.0.M2/changelog.txt">changelog</a> and <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-mobile/docs/1.1.0.M2/reference/html/">reference manual</a> for more information. Many thanks to the community for their support with regard to this new feature, including Scott Rossillo for his initial pull request and Neale Upstone for his input and feedback.</p>

<p>To retrieve the software, 
<a href="http://www.springsource.com/download/community?project=Spring%20Mobile">download</a> the release distribution, or add the <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-mobile/docs/1.1.0.M2/reference/html/spring-mobile-device.html#spring-mobile-device-howtoget">maven artifacts</a> to your project. Sample apps are available at <a href="https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-mobile-samples">github.com/SpringSource/spring-mobile-samples</a></p>

<p>If you are building a mobile web app, we encourage you try out Spring Mobile 1.1.0.M2 and <a href="http://forum.springsource.org/forumdisplay.php?f=85">collaborate</a> with us on the next iteration of the project.</p>  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
<div id="node-3784" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-sticky node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/3784" title="This Week in Spring  - January 15th, 2012">This Week in Spring  - January 15th, 2012</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Josh Long on Tue, 2013-01-15 20:22        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_14 first last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/14" rel="tag" title="">This Week in Spring</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    	 Welcome to another installment of <EM>This Week in Spring</EM>! Can you believe we're already halfway through January?  We've got a <EM>lot</EM> to cover, so let's press on!  In particular, there's a <EM>lot</EM> of great video content to keep you occupied for hours this week. Enjoy! 
	 </P> 
     <OL>
  
	<li>Join Scott Andrews as he discusses the role of Javascript in an exciting webinar on  January 24, 2013: <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3767" title="Webinar: Architecture of a Modern Web App"> Architecture of a Modern Web App</a>.</li>
	<LI>Join Brian Cavalier and John Hann as they discuss Inversion of Control (IoC) and Javascript in a Webinar on January 31, 2013: <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3768">IOC + Javascript</a>.</LI>
	<LI>The <EM>A thought with a cup of coffee!!!</EM> blog has an  introductory post  comparing   
